Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

Spread your chips out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Cumberland sausages{8} onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages.

While everything cooks, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all) and pop it into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and three quarters of the @mayonnaise{64%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix to combine.

Once the sausages are cooked, remove the tray from the oven.
> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Drizzle over the @gochujang paste{30%grams} and @honey{15%grams}. Turn the sausages so they are well coated in the glaze.
> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Transfer the gochujang and honey glazed sausages to your #plates{}.

Serve the sesame chips and coriander slaw alongside. Dollop any remaining mayo on the plate for dipping.

Enjoy!